tool.name: DailyEarthquakesPerState

param.name: in_workspace
param.dialogReference: The workspace folder where outputs should be saved.

param.name: in_date
param.dialogReference: User-defined day of interest for temporally summarizing the earthquake data.

param.name: in_feature
param.dialogReference: State census polygon feature class, "State_2010Census_DP1", which is located in the "Profile-County_Tract" geodatabase of the zipped data package. Geodatabase can be found through Tiger data webpage: (https://www.census.gov/geo/maps-data/data/tiger-data.html)

param.name: out_feature3
param.dialogReference:
Total number of earthquakes per state on the user-defined date of interest. Output is a polygon feature class. Count of points is located within the attribute table and can be symbolized on the map, or exported to a table.

Suggested output name, "QuakesPerState_yymmdd".

tool.summary: This tool converts the USGS 30-day earthquake csv file to a point feature class. Earthquakes are queried to a user-defined date. The quakes that occurred on the user-defined date are counted and the total number is summarized within user-defined boundary polygons (ex. US States).
tool.usage: For creating daily data reports on how many earthquakes occurred on a selected date within each of these United States (including Puerto Rico and the District of Columbia)

dataIdInfo.idCredit: United States Geological Survey, United States Census Bureau (Tiger dataset, 2010)
